## Enforcement Checklist

**Before editing ANY Python file in codebase, verify:**

- [ ] **Check if file has source notebook** (read first line: "Code extracted from notebooks/...")
- [ ] **If yes:** Update notebook first, then re-extract (NEVER edit codebase directly)
- [ ] **If no:** Create notebook first, then extract

**Before extracting code to codebase, verify:**

- [ ] MA Phase 1 complete (intent documented)
- [ ] MA Phase 2 complete (math foundation)
- [ ] MA Phase 3 complete (invariant + lemma)
- [ ] MA Phase 4 complete (verification notebook with implementation code)
- [ ] MA Phase 5 complete (CI enforcement)
- [ ] Code written in notebook (not codebase)
- [ ] Notebook structure follows requirements (separate cells for each component)
- [ ] Every code cell preceded by markdown cell explaining: what it is, what it does, why this approach, reasoning, expected outcome, what "good" looks like
- [ ] Functions separated (one function per cell)
- [ ] Classes separated (one class per cell)
- [ ] Imports separated (each import or import group in own cell)
- [ ] Each function tested individually (function-level test cells with markdown explanations)
