## What This Prevents

This rule prevents:
- ❌ Writing code directly in codebase and skipping notebooks
- ❌ Manually editing codebase files (use extraction script only)
- ❌ "Validating" codebase code in notebooks (reverse flow)
- ❌ Copying code from other codebase files without notebook origin
- ❌ Implementing algorithms without MA process completion
- ❌ Codebase-codebase dependencies that bypass notebooks
- ❌ Debugging code in codebase (fix in notebooks, then re-extract)
- ❌ Extracting code before all functions pass tests
- ❌ Untested or broken code entering the codebase

This rule ensures:
- ✅ Code originates in notebooks (source of truth)
- ✅ Functions are separated and individually testable
- ✅ Each function is tested individually in notebooks
- ✅ All debugging happens in notebooks (not in codebase)
- ✅ Code is validated against lemmas/invariants before extraction
- ✅ Codebase code is extracted via script (not written directly)
- ✅ Codebase only receives working, tested code
- ✅ Notebooks remain canonical and executable
- ✅ MA process is followed completely
- ✅ ALL issues are caught in notebooks before extraction

